From 6f56024e2a7adcaac911700e6f6f0a3f0a5e129e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lukas Klizas <lukas@klizas.lt>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 12:46:54 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] vga_switcheroo: drop T2 DMI defer for dGPU-equipped T2 Macs

The CachyOS 7.0.6 kernel adds a T2-Mac DMI match (t2_mac_tbl) to
vga_switcheroo_client_probe_defer() so the AMD GPU probe is deferred
even when it is the boot VGA device, and pairs it with a new
EPROBE_DEFER call in amdgpu_pci_probe(). The intent is that
apple-gmux probes first, switches the panel to the iGPU via
apple-gmux.force_igd=1, makes i915 the vga_default_device, and the
AMD GPU then stays out of the display path.

That sequence only works on T2 Macs where the iGPU is fully enabled
(i.e. apple-set-os has been applied to spoof macOS during the EFI
handoff). On 15"/16" MacBook Pros (MacBookPro15,*, MacBookPro16,1/2)
and similar dGPU-equipped T2 models running without apple-set-os, the
iGPU enumerates but has no VBT and no usable displays; i915 binds as
a stub and cannot drive the panel. The defer still fires because of
the DMI match, amdgpu's probe is delayed behind apple-gmux, and the
resulting device_link / dpm_list topology has amdgpu sequenced after
gmux for PM purposes. Resume then trips amdgpu's MODE1 hard reset
fallback and the next suspend hangs with a black panel, requiring a
forced shutdown.

Restore the pre-7.0.6 condition: defer only when pdev is not the
vga_default_device. The intended apple-set-os + force_igd flow still
works, because in that scenario gmux probes first, force_igd sets
i915 as the default, and amdgpu's later probe satisfies
pdev != vga_default_device() on its own. Dropping the DMI clause
removes the only orphan user of include/linux/cachy-t2.h from this
file.

Signed-off-by: Lukas Klizas <lukas@klizas.lt>
---
 drivers/gpu/vga/vga_switcheroo.c | 9 ++++++---
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/vga/vga_switcheroo.c b/drivers/gpu/vga/vga_switcheroo.c
index fd7f830..8fe1ae3 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/vga/vga_switcheroo.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/vga/vga_switcheroo.c
@@ -31,7 +31,6 @@
 #define pr_fmt(fmt) "vga_switcheroo: " fmt
 
 #include <linux/apple-gmux.h>
-#include <linux/cachy-t2.h>
 #include <linux/console.h>
 #include <linux/debugfs.h>
 #include <linux/fb.h>
@@ -439,8 +438,12 @@ find_active_client(struct list_head *head)
 bool vga_switcheroo_client_probe_defer(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 {
 	if (pci_is_display(pdev)) {
-		if (apple_gmux_present() && !vgasr_priv.handler_flags &&
-		    (pdev != vga_default_device() || dmi_check_system(t2_mac_tbl)))
+		/*
+		 * apple-gmux is needed on pre-retina MacBook Pro
+		 * to probe the panel if pdev is the inactive GPU.
+		 */
+		if (apple_gmux_present() && pdev != vga_default_device() &&
+		    !vgasr_priv.handler_flags)
 			return true;
 	}
 
